Structures: Resource Profiles {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR resources for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               4AT Delirium Assessment

            {% capture desc %}Rapid clinical test for delirium (4AT) comprising Alertness, AMT4, Attention, and Acute Change/Fluctuating Course. A total score of 4 or more suggests possible delirium.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               ACVPU Consciousness Level

            {% capture desc %}ACVPU consciousness level assessment for NEWS2 (Alert, Confusion, Voice, Pain, Unresponsive){% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Abbey Pain Scale

            {% capture desc %}Pain assessment for people with dementia or who cannot verbalise. Assesses 6 parameters: Vocalization, Facial Expression, Body Language, Behavioral Change, Physiological Change, Physical Changes. Total score determines pain severity (0-2 No pain, 3-7 Mild, 8-13 Moderate, 14+ Severe).{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Barthel Index

            {% capture desc %}Barthel Index for measuring independence in activities of daily living (ADL). Score 0-20=total dependency, 91-99=slight dependency, 100=independent. Total range 0-100.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Blood Pressure

            {% capture desc %}Blood pressure observation for NEWS2 (systolic BP used for scoring){% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Body Temperature

            {% capture desc %}Body temperature observation for NEWS2{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Braden Scale Assessment

            {% capture desc %}A profile for the Braden Scale pressure ulcer risk assessment{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Bristol Stool Chart

            {% capture desc %}Assessment of stool form using the Bristol Stool Chart (Types 1-7). Gold standard for bowel function assessment.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Clinical Frailty Scale (CFS)

            {% capture desc %}Assessment of frailty using the Rockwood Clinical Frailty Scale (1-9). Essential for older adults to determine baseline functional status.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Fluid Balance

            {% capture desc %}Assessment of fluid intake, output, and balance. Critical for renal function, hydration status, and heart failure monitoring.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Glasgow Coma Scale

            {% capture desc %}Glasgow Coma Scale (GCS) for assessing level of consciousness. Total score 3-15 with three required components: Eye (1-4), Verbal (1-5), Motor (1-6).{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Heart Rate

            {% capture desc %}Heart rate (pulse) observation for NEWS2{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Inspired Oxygen

            {% capture desc %}Inspired oxygen observation for NEWS2 (air vs supplemental oxygen){% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               MUST Score (Malnutrition Universal Screening Tool)

            {% capture desc %}Malnutrition Universal Screening Tool for identifying adults at risk of malnutrition. Score 0=low risk, 1=medium risk, 2+=high risk. NHS-standard nutritional screening.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Mental Capacity Assessment

            {% capture desc %}Records the outcome of a Mental Capacity Assessment for a specific decision. Fundamental legal safeguard in UK nursing practice.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Mini Mental State Examination (MMSE)

            {% capture desc %}Mini Mental State Examination for cognitive function screening. Score 24-30=no impairment, 18-23=mild, 0-17=severe. Total range 0-30.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Monk Skin Tone Observation

            {% capture desc %}Observation of patient skin tone using the Monk Skin Tone Scale (10-point scale A-J). Provides more granular skin tone assessment than Fitzpatrick scale, particularly for darker skin tones. Supports equitable care and accurate clinical assessment across diverse populations.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Morse Fall Scale

            {% capture desc %}Morse Fall Scale for assessing fall risk. Score 0-24=no risk, 25-50=low risk, ≥51=high risk. Total range 0-125.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               NEWS2 Score

            {% capture desc %}National Early Warning Score 2 (NEWS2) for detecting clinical deterioration. Fully aligned with NHS CareConnect-NEWS2-Observation-1.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               NEWS2 Sub-Score

            {% capture desc %}Individual parameter sub-score for NEWS2 (0-3 for most parameters). References the related vital sign observation.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Nursing Problem

            {% capture desc %}Nursing diagnosis or problem identified during assessment. Represents clinical judgments about individual, family, or community responses to actual or potential health problems. Part of the ADPIE framework's Diagnosis phase.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               ONC Goal Evaluation

            {% capture desc %}Explicit evaluation of whether a nursing goal was achieved, closing the ADPIE loop.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               ONC NHS Patient

            {% capture desc %}A patient profile for use in NHS nursing contexts with ethnic category extension.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               ONC Nursing Clinical Impression

            {% capture desc %}Nurse's synthesis of patient progress against care plan, aggregating multiple goal evaluations.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               ONC Nursing Goal

            {% capture desc %}Patient-centered goal with mandatory evaluation requirements. Serves as the 'spine' of the CarePlan, linking problems to outcomes.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               ONC Nursing Intervention

            {% capture desc %}Nursing intervention performed to achieve patient goals. Part of ADPIE Implementation phase.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Open Nursing Core Assessment

            {% capture desc %}Base profile for nursing assessment observations conforming to UK Core standards. Captures structured nursing assessment data as part of the ADPIE (Assessment, Diagnosis, Planning, Implementation, Evaluation) nursing process framework. Used as parent for specialized assessments like NEWS2, Braden Scale, and clinical observations.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Oral Health Assessment

            {% capture desc %}Assessment of oral cavity health. Critical for prevention of pneumonia in frail elderly and maintaining nutrition/hydration.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Oxygen Saturation

            {% capture desc %}Oxygen saturation (SpO2) observation for NEWS2{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               PBS ABC Chart

            {% capture desc %}Antecedent-Behaviour-Consequence (ABC) Chart for recording behaviours of concern. Fundamental tool in Positive Behaviour Support (PBS) for Learning Disabilities.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Pain Assessment (NRS 0-10)

            {% capture desc %}Pain severity assessment using the Numeric Rating Scale (0-10){% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Patient Story

            {% capture desc %}A narrative summary of the patient's background, biography, preferences, and personhood. Goes beyond clinical history to capture 'who the person is'.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Reasonable Adjustment

            {% capture desc %}Captures specific strict requirements for care adjustments under the Equality Act (e.g., 'Needs BSL Interpreter', 'Cannot use stairs', 'Requires large print').{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Relational Engagement Score

            {% capture desc %}Assessment of the quality and depth of the nurse-patient relationship or engagement level. Supports the relational aspect of care.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Respiration Rate

            {% capture desc %}Respiration rate observation for NEWS2{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Seizure Record

            {% capture desc %}Record of a specific seizure event, including type, duration, triggers, and recovery phases. Essential for epilepsy management and identifying patterns.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Skin Tone Observation

            {% capture desc %}Observation of patient skin tone using the Fitzpatrick skin type classification. Supports equitable care by enabling skin tone-aware clinical decision making, particularly for conditions that present differently across skin tones (e.g., pressure ulcers, cyanosis).{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Sleep Pattern

            {% capture desc %}Observation of sleep quality, duration, and disturbances. Sleep pattern disturbance is a key indicator for delirium and general wellbeing.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Urinalysis

            {% capture desc %}Point-of-care urine dipstick test results. Used to screen for urinary tract infection (UTI), diabetes (glucose/ketones), and kidney health.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Waterlow Score

            {% capture desc %}Waterlow Pressure Ulcer Risk Assessment - NHS standard tool. Score ≥10 indicates at risk, ≥15 high risk, ≥20 very high risk.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               What Matters to Me

            {% capture desc %}Captures the patient's specific, personal priorities and non-clinical goals (e.g., 'I want to walk my daughter down the aisle'). Fundamental to person-centred care.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Wound Assessment

            {% capture desc %}Comprehensive wound assessment including staging and dimensions{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               qSOFA (Quick SOFA)

            {% capture desc %}Quick Sequential Organ Failure Assessment for sepsis screening. Score ≥2 indicates high risk. Total range 0-3.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





Structures: Extension Definitions {% capture grouping_desc %}These define constraints on FHIR data types for systems conforming to this implementation guide.{% endcapture %}
    {{ grouping_desc | markdownify}}





               Intervention Goal Reference

            {% capture desc %}Extension to link nursing interventions to the patient goals they are intended to achieve.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               Observation Goal Reference

            {% capture desc %}Extension to link goal evaluation observations to the patient goals being evaluated.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}




               UK Core Ethnic Category

            {% capture desc %}An extension to record the ethnic category of a patient, as per UK Core standards.{% endcapture %}
{{ desc | markdownify}}





